.PP
\[en] title: TRACEE\-LIST section: 1 header: Tracee List Command Manual
date: 2026/07 \&...
.SS NAME
tracee \f[B]list\f[R] \- List traceable events, detectors, or policies;
inspect filtering and dependencies
.SS SYNOPSIS
tracee \f[B]list\f[R] <subcommand> [arguments\&...]
[options]
.SS DESCRIPTION
The \f[B]list\f[R] command displays available events, detectors, or
policies that can be used with Tracee, and inspects where an event\[cq]s
filters are enforced and how its dependencies resolve.
.PP
A subcommand is required.
.SS SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
\f[B]events\f[R] [filters\&...]
List all traceable events with optional filtering.
See tracee\-list\-events(1).
.TP
\f[B]detectors\f[R] [paths\&...]
List available detectors from built\-in and YAML sources.
See tracee\-list\-detectors(1).
.TP
\f[B]policies\f[R] [paths\&...]
List policies from directories or files.
See tracee\-list\-policies(1).
.TP
\f[B]filterable\f[R] [event\&... | policy\-path\&...]
Show which event fields filter in the kernel vs user space, or analyze
where a policy\[cq]s selected events are filtered.
See tracee\-list\-filterable(1).
.TP
\f[B]deps\f[R] <event\&...>
Show an event\[cq]s dependency graph (tree, mermaid, or json).
See tracee\-list\-deps(1).
.SS EXAMPLES
.IP \[bu] 2
List all events:
.IP
.EX
tracee list events
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
List events with filters:
.IP
.EX
tracee list events tag=fs
tracee list events type=detector threat.severity=critical
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
List detectors:
.IP
.EX
tracee list detectors
tracee list detectors ./my\-detectors
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
List policies:
.IP
.EX
tracee list policies
tracee list policies ./my\-policies
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
Show where an event\[cq]s fields filter, or analyze a policy:
.IP
.EX
tracee list filterable security_file_open
tracee list filterable ./my\-policies
.EE
.IP \[bu] 2
Show an event\[cq]s dependency graph:
.IP
.EX
tracee list deps net_packet_icmp
tracee list deps sched_process_exec \-\-format mermaid
.EE
